# Super Mario Vejlupek

Funny Platformer project by Vali and Jasmi.

## How to run the game

You can play the game directly in your browser by visiting the GitHub Pages site:
https://[your-github-username].github.io/supermariovejlupek/

Alternatively, you can run the game locally by opening the `index.html` file in your browser.

## Game Controls

- **Move Left**: Left Arrow or A
- **Move Right**: Right Arrow or D
- **Jump**: Up Arrow, W, or Space
- **Fullscreen**: Click the Fullscreen button in the top-right corner

## Game Features

- Platform jumping gameplay
- Enemies to defeat
- Boss battle at the end of the level who throws bananas
- Responsive design that works on different screen sizes

## Development

This game is built using HTML5 Canvas and JavaScript. The code is organized into modules:

- `game.js` - Main game engine
- `player.js` - Player character logic
- `enemy.js` - Enemy behavior
- `boss.js` - Boss character and banana projectiles
- `platform.js` - Platform and level generation
- `input.js` - Input handling
- `utils.js` - Utility functions

## Continuous Deployment

This project uses GitHub Actions to automatically deploy the game to GitHub Pages whenever changes are pushed to the main branch. The workflow:

1. Checks out the repository
2. Creates a distribution directory
3. Minifies JavaScript and CSS files for better performance
4. Deploys the game to GitHub Pages

You can see the deployment workflow in `.github/workflows/deploy.yml`.

